<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-52-0533 </DOCNO><TEXT>Definitions of air pollution terminology, such as pollution, emissionand dispersion are explained. Methods of detection of air pollutantsand damages by air pollutants are outlined with typical examples focusingon the dispersion of air pollutants, analytical methods, and bioindicators.Special attention was given to the use of cryptogams as bioindicatorsof air pollution stress. A recent study on the vegetation of cryptogamousepiphytes in the township of Zurich is presented and compared with ananalogous study originating from 1936.</TEXT></DOC>